        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The specific algorithm used is as follows."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Categories are determined by first checking which of boolean,\ninteger (int/uint), or floating point (float/complex) the maximum\nkind of all the arrays and the scalars are."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "If there are only scalars or the maximum category of the scalars\nis higher than the maximum category of the arrays,\nthe data types are combined with "
              },
              {
                "display_text": "promote_types",
                "explicit_title": false,
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/promote_types",
                "kind": "role_reference",
                "original_target": "promote_types",
                "role": "func",
                "suppress_link": false,
                "target": "promote_types",
                "unresolved": false
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nto produce the return value."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Otherwise, "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/min_scalar_type",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "min_scalar_type",
                "text": "min_scalar_type"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is called on each scalar, and\nthe resulting data types are all combined with "
              },
              {
                "display_text": "promote_types",
                "explicit_title": false,
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/promote_types",
                "kind": "role_reference",
                "original_target": "promote_types",
                "role": "func",
                "suppress_link": false,
                "target": "promote_types",
                "unresolved": false
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "\nto produce the return value."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The set of int values is not a subset of the uint values for types\nwith the same number of bits, something not reflected in\n"
              },
              {
                "display_text": "min_scalar_type",
                "explicit_title": false,
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/min_scalar_type",
                "kind": "role_reference",
                "original_target": "min_scalar_type",
                "role": "func",
                "suppress_link": false,
                "target": "min_scalar_type",
                "unresolved": false
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", but handled as a special case in "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/result_type",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "result_type",
                "text": "result_type"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
